OL,3,CNo apologies for devolved spending,
OL,4,Csays Keir Starmer after leaked memo
OL,6,FSir Keir Starmer has said he will
OL,7,F"make no apologies" for spending in
OL,8,Fdevolved areas following outcry over a
OL,9,Fleaked Downing Street memo.
OL,11,FPlaid Cymru leader Rhun ap Iorwerth
OL,12,Faccused the Prime Minister of a
OL,13,F"direct assault" on devolution as he
OL,14,Fraised the memo during First
OL,15,FMinister's Questions in the Senedd on
OL,16,FTuesday, 10 March.
OL,26,@oD@AOUoD@SO]uD@AOUuD@PO]
