OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F463A1773349953
OL,3,CNo apologies for devolved spending,
OL,4,Csays Keir Starmer after leaked memo
OL,6,FSent in December to all members of the
OL,7,FUK Government Cabinet, the
OL,8,Fcorrespondence said: "Each of us will
OL,9,Fmaintain a professional and respectful
OL,10,Fworking relationship with our
OL,11,Fcounterparts in devolved governments.
OL,13,F"However, an overly deferential or
OL,14,Flaissez-faire approach to devolved
OL,15,Fgovernment engagement almost
OL,16,Finevitably creates political
OL,17,Fchallenges or misses positive
OL,18,Fopportunities.
OL,26,@pD@VOUuD@AOU
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G2/8
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,464,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F463A1773349953
OL,3,CNo apologies for devolved spending,
OL,4,Csays Keir Starmer after leaked memo
OL,6,F"We should be confident in our ability
OL,7,Fto deliver directly in those nations,
OL,8,Fincluding through direct spending,
OL,9,Feven when devolved governments may
OL,10,Foppose this."
OL,12,FThe memo was condemned in both Wales
OL,13,Fand Scotland when it was made public,
OL,14,Fbut challenged on the issue at Prime
OL,15,FMinister's Questions on Wednesday by
OL,16,FSNP MP Stephen Gethins, Sir Keir said:
OL,17,F"I'm not going to make any apologies
OL,18,Ffor spending more money in Scotland,
OL,19,For in Wales, to improve people's
OL,20,Flives."
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@MO]yD@AOU
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G3/8
